----------------------------------------------------------------
# Railway Postgres - LOCAL CONNECTION (pgAdmin, Django from laptop)
#
# postgres-jfon.railway.internal = INTERNAL ONLY (getaddrinfo failed from laptop)
# You MUST use the TCP Proxy host/port below.
#
# SETUP: Railway Dashboard > Postgres service > Settings > Networking
#   - Add "TCP Proxy" (NOT regular domain)
#   - Point to port 5432
#   - Copy the generated host (e.g. xxx.up.railway.app) and port
#   - Paste below, then copy these vars into .env
----------------------------------------------------------------

# REPLACE with your TCP Proxy host from Railway (e.g. postgres-xxx.up.railway.app)
RAILWAY_PUBLIC_HOST=REPLACE_WITH_TCP_PROXY_HOST
# REPLACE with TCP Proxy port (may be 5432 or a random port Railway assigns)
RAILWAY_PUBLIC_PORT=REPLACE_WITH_TCP_PROXY_PORT

# Use these for local Django / pgAdmin (copy to .env):
# DATABASE_PUBLIC_URL=postgresql://postgres:uPjNNwXNImDEmUJdDptCyBmVEQJssurr@REPLACE_HOST:REPLACE_PORT/railway
# pgAdmin: Host=RAILWAY_PUBLIC_HOST, Port=RAILWAY_PUBLIC_PORT

----------------------------------------------------------------
# Internal (for app deployed ON Railway - do not use from laptop)
----------------------------------------------------------------
PGHOST=postgres-jfon.railway.internal
PGPORT=5432
PGUSER=postgres
POSTGRES_DB=railway
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=uPjNNwXNImDEmUJdDptCyBmVEQJssurr
POSTGRES_USER=postgres

DB_HOST=postgres-jfon.railway.internal
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=railway
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=uPjNNwXNImDEmUJdDptCyBmVEQJssurr
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:uPjNNwXNImDEmUJdDptCyBmVEQJssurr@postgres-jfon.railway.internal:5432/railway
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:uPjNNwXNImDEmUJdDptCyBmVEQJssurr@crossover.proxy.rlwy.net:58324/railway

Connect to your service over TCP using a proxied domain and port
crossover.proxy.rlwy.net:58324 :5432




